		"description": "<p>Choose either&nbsp;scars or scourge, and then choose one of&nbsp;the following damage types: acid, cold,&nbsp;fire, force, lightning, necrotic, poison,&nbsp;psychic, radiant, or thunder.</p>\n<p><em>Scars: </em>You have resistance to the&nbsp;chosen damage type.</p>\n<p><em>Scourge: </em>As a bonus action, you can&nbsp;enhance the next attack you make this&nbsp;turn. If that attack hits, it deals extra&nbsp;damage of the chosen type equal to&nbsp;your proficiency bonus. However, the&nbsp;sting of the scourge lessens after the&nbsp;initial strike, so after you deal this extra&nbsp;damage to a creature, this trait cannot&nbsp;deal extra damage to it during the same&nbsp;combat</p>",
